  "id": "CENTRAL-CLRA",
  "name": "Contract Labour (Regulation and Abolition) Act, 1970",
  "shortName": "CLRA Act",
  "officialCitation": "The Contract Labour (Regulation and Abolition) Act, 1970, repealed and saved under section 143 of the Occupational Safety, Health and Working Conditions Code, 2020.",
  "overview": "Historical central labour-law record governing registration of principal employers, contractor licensing and contract-worker welfare before the Occupational Safety, Health and Working Conditions Code, 2020 became operative on 21 November 2025. The Contract Labour (Regulation and Abolition) Act, 1970 was repealed under section 143 of the OSHWC Code, subject to savings. Current contract-labour obligations must be evaluated under Chapter XI, Part I of the OSHWC Code and the applicable Central, State or Union Territory rules and notifications. This record is retained for historical periods, saved licences and registrations, pending proceedings and audit traceability.",
